Cook said, "Following the increases in stamp duty on high-priced homes and the introduction of associated anti-bypass legislation, it's hard to argue high-value properties are under-taxed, notwithstanding the impact of the outdated council tax system."
"But this move could make some foreign investors more reluctant to buy property in London or discourage owners from selling," he added.
